cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper deals with improving the generalization of neural networks in the presence of label noise. It proposes a method to quantify the amount of memorized information about the noise in the network weights and shows that reducing this information leads to better generalization. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization techniques and their limitations, which is relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
